casebody.data:
EDWARD B. SWEENEY, APPELLANT, v. LOUIS G. GRISSLER, RESPONDENT. Decided May 11, 1929.

Before Justices Tbenchaed, Kalisch and Lloyd.

Eor the appellant, Earl A. Merrill. Eor the respondent, no appearance. Pee Cueiam.

This appeal should be dismissed. There is no agreed state of the case between the attorneys of the respective parties, nor is there a state of the case settled by the trial judge.

Appeal is dismissed, with costs.
